#: ../../../module_file_support.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Learn how to configure and customize module file generation in Spack for "
"Environment Modules and Lmod."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../module_file_support.rst:13
msgid "Modules (modules.yaml)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../module_file_support.rst:15
msgid ""
"The use of module systems to manage user environments in a controlled way is "
"a common practice at HPC centers that is sometimes embraced also by "
"individual programmers on their development machines. To support this common "
"practice Spack integrates with `Environment Modules <http://modules."
"sourceforge.net/>`_ and `Lmod <http://lmod.readthedocs.io/en/latest/>`_ by "
"providing post-install hooks that generate module files and commands to "
"manipulate them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../module_file_support.rst:18
msgid ""
"Modules are one of several ways you can use Spack packages. For other "
"options that may fit your use case better, you should also look at :ref:"
"`spack load <spack-load>` and :ref:`environments <environments>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../module_file_support.rst:22
msgid "Quick start"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../module_file_support.rst:24
msgid ""
"In the current version of Spack, module files are not generated by default. "
"To get started, you can generate module files for all currently installed "
"packages by running either"
msgstr ""

